"title": "2318: Jesus Christ, as prophet",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2318: jesus christ, as prophet",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ was acclaimed as a prophet by those who witnessed his miracles and heard his teaching. They recognised him as a bearer of the word of God, who spoke with authority concerning the nature and purposes of God.</p>\n<h2>Examples of those who recognised Jesus Christ as a prophet</h2>\n<h3>People anticipating the coming prophet</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:14\">JHN 6:14</a></strong> <em>The reference is to the promised prophet, who, like Moses, would see God face to face (see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:15,Deut18:18\">Dt 18:15,18</a>).</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:21\">JHN 1:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:40\">JHN 7:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:52\">JHN 7:52</a></p>\n<h3>A Samaritan woman</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:17-John4:19\">JHN 4:17–4:19</a></p>\n<h3>Witnesses of Jesus Christ's miracles</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:1-Matt14:5\">MAT 14:1–14:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:14-Mark6:15\">MRK 6:14–6:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:13-Matt16:14\">MAT 16:13–16:14</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:27-Mark8:28\">MRK 8:27–8:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:18-Luke9:19\">LUK 9:18–9:19</a></p>\n<h3>The crowd as Jesus Christ approached Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:10-Matt21:11\">MAT 21:10–21:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:46\">MAT 21:46</a></p>\n<h3>Two of Jesus Christ's disciples after his death</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:19\">LUK 24:19</a></p>\n<h3>The apostles Peter and Stephen</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:20-Acts3:23\">ACT 3:20–3:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:37\">ACT 7:37</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:15-Deut18:18\">DEU 18:15–18:18</a></p>\n<h2>Indications of Jesus Christ being a prophet</h2>\n<h3>He announced coming blessing from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:37-John7:40\">JHN 7:37–7:40</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:3-Matt5:12\">MAT 5:3–5:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:20-Luke6:23\">LUK 6:20–6:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:16-Matt13:17\">MAT 13:16–13:17</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:23-Luke10:24\">LUK 10:23–10:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:19-John20:21\">JHN 20:19–20:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:29\">JHN 20:29</a></p>\n<h3>He announced coming judgment and woe</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:23\">ACT 3:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:20-Matt11:24\">MAT 11:20–11:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:13-Luke10:15\">LUK 10:13–10:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:13-Matt23:39\">MAT 23:13–23:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:24-Luke6:26\">LUK 6:24–6:26</a></p>\n<h3>He possessed supernatural knowledge and insight</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:24-John2:25\">JHN 2:24–2:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:4\">MAT 9:4</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:8\">MRK 2:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:22\">LUK 5:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:39-Luke7:43\">LUK 7:39–7:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:47\">LUK 9:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:16-John4:19\">JHN 4:16–4:19</a></p>\n<h3>He performed mighty works and miracles</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:12-Luke7:17\">LUK 7:12–7:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:17\">JHN 9:17</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's own understanding of himself as a prophet</h2>\n<h3>As a rejected prophet</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:31-Luke13:35\">LUK 13:31–13:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:57\">MAT 13:57</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:4\">MRK 6:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:24-Luke4:27\">LUK 4:24–4:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:46\">JHN 5:46</a></p>\n<h3>As a prophet anointed by God's Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:34\">JHN 3:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:16-Luke4:21\">LUK 4:16–4:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1-Isa61:2\">ISA 61:1–61:2</a></p>\n<h3>As a prophet who speaks with authority</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:22\">MRK 1:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:28\">MRK 3:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:16\">JHN 7:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:10\">JHN 14:10</a></p>\n<h2>The place of Jesus Christ in relation to other prophets</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is greater than other prophets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:41\">MAT 12:41</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:32\">LUK 11:32</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:15\">JHN 1:15</a> <em>John the Baptist was accepted as a prophet (e.g., <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:9\">Mt 11:9</a>).</em></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is the Messiah and Son of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:13-Matt16:17\">MAT 16:13–16:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:1-Heb1:2\">HEB 1:1–1:2</a></p>\n<h3>The exalted Christ is the source and essence of all prophecy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:10\">REV 19:10</a></p>",
